Privacy Policy for PriceWise

This Privacy Policy explains how PriceWise ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and protects information in connection with the Price Comparison App.

1. Information We Collect

We only collect information necessary to provide the core functionality of price comparison, user accounts, and service improvement.

A. Information You Provide Directly

  • Account Information: If you use login/signup (Q5), we collect your email/username and a securely hashed password.
  • Favorite Items/Price Alerts: We store product IDs and price alert settings in our database to manage your saved items.

B. Information Collected Automatically (Usage Data)

  • Search History: We store your queries to improve search performance, filtering, and Trie autocomplete training.
  • Interaction Data: We log statistics on filter usage (In Store Only, Lowest Price), sorting methods, and clicks to external retailers.
  • Technical Information: Standard information like IP address, browser type, and device type is logged for security and monitoring purposes (Q8).

2. How We Use Your Information

We use the collected data for the following purposes:

  • Service Delivery: To aggregate prices, display search results, and manage your saved item lists and preferences.
  • Service Improvement: To analyze search patterns to improve the accuracy and speed of our advanced data structures (Trie, Caching Layer) and optimize API calls.
  • Security and Authentication: To verify user identity, protect your account with securely hashed passwords (Q6), and manage authentication tokens (JWTs).

3. Third-Party API Integration and Data Sharing

The core function of PriceWise relies on sending your search query to external service providers.

  • Retailer APIs (Amazon, Walmart, Best Buy, etc. - Q3): Your raw search query is sent to these third-party APIs to fetch real-time price data. We do not control how these third parties use the search data they receive.
  • Anonymous Search: We do not send your personal account details (email or user ID) to these APIs. All search requests are made anonymously by our backend server.
  • External Links: When you click a "Link Button," you are redirected to the external retailer's website. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those sites.

4. Data Storage and Security

We are committed to protecting your data, using the methods outlined in our project plan:

  • Password Protection: Passwords are never stored in plain text; they are secured using a secure hashing algorithm (Q6).
  • API Keys and Secrets: All sensitive credentials, including third-party API keys, are stored in environment variables during deployment on Render (Q6, Q7).
  • Transmission Security: All data transmission between your browser and our server is encrypted using HTTPS (Q6).

5. Changes to This Policy

We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy. We will notify you of any significant changes by updating the "Last Updated" date at the top of this document.

6. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this policy, please contact us @ jlaua2@uic.edu, mjame5@uic.edu, ayous11@uic.edu and jrodr300@uic.edu.
